headline: Activist Elliott Names Nominees for Phillips 66 Board Amid Proxy Fight
summary: Activist investor Elliott Investment Management disclosed the names of its four nominees to join Phillips 66’ board of directors, in a move that comes shortly after it sued the oil refiner and its board for seat changes.

headline: Elliott Sends Letter to Shareholders and Mails Definitive Proxy Materials Outlining Why Board Change is Needed at Phillips 66
summary: Elliott Investment Management L.P. ("Elliott"), which manages funds that together have an investment of more than $2.5 billion in Phillips 66 (NYSE: PSX) (the "Company" or "Phillips"), today sent a letter to the Company's shareholders highlighting why change is urgently needed on the Phillips Board of Directors (the "Board").
